      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:3:63:1",
      "text": [
        " إِنَّ أَمِيرَ الْمُؤْمِنِينَ ( عليه السلام ) أَمَرَ قَنْبَرَ أَنْ يَضْرِبَ رَجُلًا حَدّاً فَغَلُظَ قَنْبَرٌ فَزَادَهُ ثَلَاثَةَ أَسْوَاطٍ فَأَقَادَهُ عَلِيٌّ ( عليه السلام ) مِنْ قَنْبَرٍ ثَلَاثَةَ أَسْوَاطٍ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad, from Ibn Mahboub, from Al Hassan Bin Salih Al Sowry, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Ja’far<sup>asws</sup> having said that Amir Al-Momineen<sup>asws</sup> ordered Qanbar that he should whip a man, a Penalty (<span class=\"iTxt\">Hadd</span>). So Qanbar was harsh, and increased by three lashes. So Ali<sup>asws</sup> caused retaliation from Qanbar of the three (excessive) lashes’."
        ]
      }
    }
